title.narrative: 4.2 Government and other service providers (social welfare and justice sectors) are better able to deliver quality gender-sensitivechild protection prevention and response services.

description.narrative: In 2021, the number of districts with social workers demonstrating quality skills in case management increased from 4 in 2020 to 8. UNICEF’s technical and financial assistance to the Government of Sierra Leone and other social welfare and justice service providers helped strengthen and ensure continuity of quality gender-sensitive child protection and response essential services including mental health and psychosocial support (MHPSS), case management, legal aid, justice services and life skills training among children in selected communities reaching 33,425 children (18,861 girls; 14,564 boys) despite challenges caused by COVID-19 and several disasters which affected the country.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:03/02/2022
